            <title>[JCR-190] Caching in QueryHandler does not scale well</title>
                <link>https://issues.apache.org/jira/browse/JCR-190</link>
                <project id="10591" key="JCR">Jackrabbit Content Repository</project>
                        <description>Caching in class CachingIndexReader uses too much memory. It uses around 500 bytes per node and does not use any strategy to limit the cache.&lt;br/&gt;
&lt;br/&gt;
This improvement covers two goals:&lt;br/&gt;
- lower per-node memory cost for caching&lt;br/&gt;
- implement a caching strategy using e.g LRU algorithm</description>
